scattered clouds most of the day, clearing an hour before
sunset; low wind, 0-4 mph, from southwest; seeing 1.8" to 
2.1" at start, improving to 1.6" early on and even better
as the night went on

wind occasionally got up to 11 mph after midnight, but was
mostly < 8 mph; sky was totally clear for entire light curve
and seeing stayed very good, a couple of times < 1.3"

ref star #3 in image 475 is close to saturation but, if so,
it's negligible - no significant effect seen in light curve;
no other saturated images

image 509 nearly double-humped, but photometry looks good,
when using the optimum aperture size of 2.25 x the average
fwhm

No significant CR's landed close to 2M0753 itself or to any
of the reference stars
